WEBVTT

00:00.494 --> 00:01.794
<i>Previously on</i> Heartland:

00:01.795 --> 00:04.195
Clint: I have to take Georgina
back to the group home

00:04.299 --> 00:05.965
until further arrangements
can be made.

00:06.033 --> 00:07.434
No. No, Grandpa.

00:07.501 --> 00:09.436
She can stay here
for a couple of days...

00:09.503 --> 00:10.937
<i>I guess.</i>

00:11.004 --> 00:12.138
<i>Dan:</i> <i>You should
know</i> <i>that Lisa and I</i>

00:12.206 --> 00:13.940
will be keeping
our finances separate.

00:14.007 --> 00:16.743
Isn't that a given considering
you guys are divorced?

00:16.811 --> 00:18.745
Now that we've reconciled,

00:18.813 --> 00:20.714
we may be pooling
our resources.

00:20.781 --> 00:25.283
I already bought the place
that you liked in France.

00:25.352 --> 00:27.553
What about us?
Where does that leave us?

00:27.620 --> 00:30.522
We should take a break,
don't you think?

00:33.693 --> 00:36.462
(Grass rustles in the breeze,
horses whinny)

00:37.396 --> 00:39.464
(Birds chirp,
insects buzz)

00:46.271 --> 00:47.605
(Horse neighs)

00:49.641 --> 00:51.476
(Soft thudding of hooves)

00:59.417 --> 01:00.484
(Leaves rustle)

01:01.719 --> 01:03.119
(Log clunks)

01:03.187 --> 01:04.421
(Foal whinnies, panicked)

01:06.290 --> 01:07.657
(Foal whinnies)

01:09.860 --> 01:11.927
(Log bangs around)

01:15.965 --> 01:17.533
(Snorts nervously)

01:19.870 --> 01:21.537
Lou:
Okay, Grandpa! Eat!

01:21.605 --> 01:23.506
Didn't you guys wanna get
an early start?

01:23.573 --> 01:25.440
Jack: Well, I wouldn't mind
a cup of coffee first.

01:25.508 --> 01:26.641
<i>Lou:</i>
<i>Amy! Ty!</i>

01:26.709 --> 01:28.142
I have been trying
to keep the eggs warm.

01:28.210 --> 01:29.744
Amy:
Relax, Lou.

01:29.812 --> 01:31.312
Grandpa, we've got the truck
all packed.

01:31.380 --> 01:32.213
I'm gonna load Spartan
and Harley

01:32.281 --> 01:33.314
before we leave.

01:33.382 --> 01:34.682
Jack:
Why are we taking horses?

01:34.750 --> 01:36.785
We're going to Stumpy's
fishing camp to work,

01:36.852 --> 01:38.986
not to go on a leisurely
trail ride.

01:39.054 --> 01:40.722
Is that why you're taking
your fishing gear?

01:40.790 --> 01:43.323
Well, if there's time,
and that is a big if,

01:43.391 --> 01:46.827
yes, I thought I would do
a little bit of fishing.

01:46.895 --> 01:48.061
Peter: So what's,
uh, Stumpy's story

01:48.129 --> 01:49.630
that he's got you doing
all this, Jack?

01:49.697 --> 01:51.364
Jack: Oh, he's got a
big family reunion

01:51.433 --> 01:52.666
coming up this weekend

01:52.734 --> 01:55.502
and the guy just broke
his good leg.

01:55.570 --> 01:57.370
There's all these tents
that need putting up,

01:57.438 --> 01:59.104
and I thought that was
the least we could do for him.

02:04.511 --> 02:06.011
Georgie: Look at the
rod Jack bought me!

02:06.079 --> 02:07.379
He's gonna teach me
to fly fish.

02:07.448 --> 02:08.981
Ty:
Really.

02:09.049 --> 02:10.316
I thought it was all work,
Jack?

02:10.383 --> 02:11.717
(Chuckling)

02:11.785 --> 02:12.952
Georgie: Come on,
guys, we have to go!

02:13.019 --> 02:14.753
Georgie,
eat some breakfast!

02:14.821 --> 02:16.955
Georgie: No!
I don't wanna barf in the truck.

02:17.022 --> 02:18.323
Ty: Okay.
I just lost my appetite.

02:18.390 --> 02:19.458
(Laughing)

02:19.525 --> 02:20.859
I'm gonna go load
the horses.

02:20.927 --> 02:22.928
Georgie: Hey, Katie,
are you gonna miss us?

02:22.995 --> 02:24.095
You're gonna miss us,
huh?

02:24.163 --> 02:25.163
(Katie coos)

02:27.667 --> 02:29.667
Miss them?
I can't wait until they leave.

02:29.734 --> 02:31.034
Stop it.

02:31.102 --> 02:32.069
Okay, everybody,
let's get this show on the road.

02:32.136 --> 02:33.604
You're gonna be late.

02:33.672 --> 02:36.440
Georgie: Exactly! Come on!
Hurry up! Come on!

02:36.508 --> 02:38.776
(Car rumbles)

02:39.578 --> 02:42.012
<i>Lou:</i> <i>Don't forget your snacks...
</i> <i>And have a great day.</i>

02:42.080 --> 02:43.581
Yeah.
Have fun out there!

02:43.648 --> 02:45.248
(Knocking)

02:45.316 --> 02:47.316
Jack: Now, where are my gloves?
I left them right here.

02:47.384 --> 02:48.885
Georgie: You don't need your gloves.
Let's go!

02:48.953 --> 02:52.221
(Knocking,
screen door snaps shut)

02:52.289 --> 02:54.457
<i>Jack: Clint!</i>
Clint: I knocked but...

02:54.525 --> 02:56.593
Uh, no, I'm glad
to see you, man,

02:56.660 --> 02:58.495
but bad timing.

02:58.562 --> 03:00.196
We're just on our way out.

03:00.263 --> 03:01.497
But, Jack,
today is the day.

03:01.564 --> 03:03.031
The day for what?

03:03.099 --> 03:04.967
Uh, this, this in the only day
I have to...

03:05.034 --> 03:07.035
<i>Spend some time with you.</i>

03:07.103 --> 03:08.737
Georgie: What does he mean?
He can't!

03:08.805 --> 03:10.572
Clint: I left you a message.
Didn't you get it?

03:10.640 --> 03:11.940
<i>Jack:</i>
<i>No, I never got a message.</i>

03:14.844 --> 03:16.645
Oh, Georgie...

03:16.713 --> 03:18.046
Clint:
Jack, I'm serious.

03:18.114 --> 03:20.215
This is the day we have
to accomplish, you know,

03:20.282 --> 03:21.682
<i>what we discussed.</i>

03:21.750 --> 03:23.784
Jack: I know, I know.
You're right.

03:23.852 --> 03:25.487
Georgie: Wait.
Does this mean you can't go camping?

03:25.554 --> 03:27.822
It means we can't go camping.

03:27.890 --> 03:29.424
Does this mean you're not
going away for the weekend?

03:30.826 --> 03:31.893
You promised!

03:33.529 --> 03:37.831
Um, Grandpa, can I speak to you,
privately, please?

03:41.369 --> 03:44.038
I thought that you were already
Georgie's foster parent?

03:44.105 --> 03:47.841
Temporary foster parent,
but I wanna be long term.

03:47.909 --> 03:49.576
I didn't even know
you'd applied.

03:49.644 --> 03:51.310
Isn't this something
we should've decided together,

03:51.378 --> 03:53.146
as a family?

03:53.213 --> 03:56.082
Jack: It's something I decided
to do and I'm gonna do it.

03:56.150 --> 03:57.816
So Clint's here
to interview me,

03:57.884 --> 04:00.153
and he needs to talk
to Georgie too,

04:00.220 --> 04:02.855
but he can't tell her
the reason because...

04:02.923 --> 04:04.590
Well, we don't want her
to get her hopes up.

04:04.658 --> 04:06.558
Okay. Well, we'll have
to cancel the trip then.

04:06.625 --> 04:07.759
Ty:
Whoa! What?

04:07.826 --> 04:09.094
No, that's not
a good idea.

04:09.162 --> 04:11.663
'Cause I think it's unfair
to go without her.

04:11.730 --> 04:14.232
But, Jack, you promised Stumpy
that we'd get those tents up.

04:14.300 --> 04:15.934
Yeah!

04:16.000 --> 04:17.202
Jack: Well, you and Amy, you
could do that job can't you?

04:17.269 --> 04:19.303
<i>Why don't you guys go up</i>
<i>on your own?</i>

04:19.372 --> 04:20.872
Yeah.

04:20.940 --> 04:22.473
<i>Amy:</i>
<i>Okay.</i>

04:22.541 --> 04:23.607
(Lou sighs heavily)

04:25.577 --> 04:27.411
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

04:29.514 --> 04:31.715
- You and I.
- You and me.

04:35.187 --> 04:36.687
(Door clicks open)

04:39.123 --> 04:40.623
(Backpack rustles)

